# Work Items — Conventions

## Template

Each work item follows the standard template. See `docs/roadmap/F00 - Development Environment and Structure/F00 - W01 - Comprehensive Documentation.md` as a reference example.

## Required structure

1. Header with Feature, Release, Sprint, Type, Priority, Estimate, Assignable to
2. Description (1-3 paragraphs)
3. Tasks with checkboxes grouped by logical section
4. Relevant technical sections (endpoints, DTOs, diagrams)
5. Acceptance Criteria with checkboxes
6. Dependencies (Blocks / Prerequisites)
7. Italic footer: `*{ID} - {Title} — Legal Ai Ar*`

## Location

- Folder: `docs/roadmap/F{XX} - {Feature Name}/`
- File: `F{XX} - W{YY} - {Title}.md`
- Sequential numbering (check the last existing W)

## Language rule

- Work item content must be written in **English** (titles, descriptions, tasks, acceptance criteria, technical sections).
- Only end-user facing UI strings referenced within work items stay in Spanish.

## Consult before generating

- `docs/roadmap/features.md` for feature and release context
- Existing work items of the same feature to keep consistency
